Yet both epithets are needed here: for the ancient champions of the immortality of the soul, chiefly the Platonists and Pythagoream, held that the life of the soul ⁶ extends backwards into the infinite past as well as forwards into the endless 'future ’ (Archer-Hind's Phaedo p. 19) 3 while the modern popular belief is that the soul was born, or created, but will never die.
